sentences: Winston Alfaro Brown Jr. (born October 3, 1965), better known by his stage name Gaby, is a Panamanian Reggae en Español and Reggaeton singer and rapper.
He is best known for his 1992 single "Meneaíto" which was a major hit record throughout South and Central America.
Gaby left the music scene in 1998.
However, he made a return in 2016.
Gaby currently resides in Atlanta.
Gaby was born on October 3, 1965, in Río Abajo, a corregimiento within the city of Panama City, Panama.
Gaby also played baseball, as well as soccer, throughout his teenage years.
After high school, Gaby majored in graphic design for three years at the  Universidad de Panamá before leaving school to begin his music career.
Gaby, as well as many other Panamanian musicians of the day, found inspiration in local artists like  Renato who were performing lyrics in español over Jamaican riddims.
Gaby and Orlando eventually established a mobile disco called SOS (Super Original Sound) and host picnics at parks during the nighttime called "paseo nocturnos".
In 1987, Gaby formed a local group called "Sweet Edition".
The group released their self-titled first album with Tamayo Records in 1987.
Sweet Edition released a second album called DURO DE MATAR in 1989, but found their music careers disrupted by the United States invasion of Panama.
In 1990, Tamayo Records released "El Meneíto" to other countries through the Colombian label "Discos Fuentes".
It spent 11 months as the number one song in Venezuela without Gaby being aware that his record had become a hit.
Gaby, and the rest of the crew, toured extensively throughout South and Central America for years afterwards.
In 1995, the relationship between Gaby and his manager, Luis, deteriorated to the point that they were no longer able to work together.
Despite his best efforts, Gaby was unable to rebuild the same level of momentum from previous years and was unable to support himself, or his family, as a musician.

In 1998, Gaby moved with his family to Germany to make a fresh start.
He remained in Germany for nine years.
He moved to Las Vegas in 2007 and worked at the  Trump Hotel.
Gaby made intermittent attempts to do music again, but did not become serious about performing until 2016.
Gaby has recorded and released several new singles, made a number of recent media appearances, and has done a number of live performances since 2016.
